 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Phase 3 to Phase 6: End-to-End Pipeline (Days 9 - 21)\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook orchestrates the entire pipeline for data cleaning, feature engineering, saving processed data, baseline modeling, and training advanced LightGBM/XGBoost ensemble models to handle class imbalance natively."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add root directory to path to access src\n",
    "sys.path.append(os.path.abspath('..'))\n",
    "\n",
    "from src.data_loader import load_data_chunked\n",
    "from src.preprocessing import preprocess_pipeline\n",
    "from src.modeling import split_data, train_baselines, train_advanced_models"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Data Loading (Day 2 recap)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "dataset_path = r\"C:\\Users\\siddp\\Downloads\\Dataset for default loan prediction\\loan.csv\"\n",
    "df_raw = load_data_chunked(dataset_path)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Preprocessing & Feature Engineering (Phases 3 & 4)\n",
    "This includes:\n",
    "- Missing Value Imputation\n",
    "- Winsorization of outliers (`annual_inc`)\n",
    "- Engineering `income_to_loan_ratio`\n",
    "- Ordinal & Frequency Encoding\n",
    "- Variance Threshold feature selection"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if df_raw is not None:\n",
    "    df_processed = preprocess_pipeline(df_raw)\n",
    "    print(\"Processed Data Shape:\", df_processed.shape)\n",
    "    display(df_processed.head())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Save Processed Data to Parquet (Day 17)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if df_raw is not None:\n",
    "    output_dir = r\"C:\\Users\\siddp\\Downloads\\HackRush_2026\\Retail_Loan_Default_Prediction\\data\"\n",
    "    os.makedirs(output_dir, exist_ok=True)\n",
    "    output_path = os.path.join(output_dir, \"processed_loan_data.parquet\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f\"Saving to {output_path}...\")\n",
    "    df_processed.to_parquet(output_path, index=False)\n",
    "    print(\"Save complete!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Modeling Pipeline (Phases 5 & 6)\n",
    "First, we split the data cleanly using Stratified splits."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if df_raw is not None:\n",
    "    X_train, X_val, X_test, y_train, y_val, y_test = split_data(df_processed)\n",
    "    print(f\"Train default rate: {y_train.mean():.4f}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Val default rate: {y_val.mean():.4f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Baseline Models (Day 20)\n",
    "To prevent memory crashes on local machines, baseline models (Logistic Regression, Decision Tree) will be trained on a subsample of 200,000 rows."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if df_raw is not None:\n",
    "    baseline_results, baseline_models = train_baselines(X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val, sample_size=200000)\n",
    "    display(baseline_results)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Advanced Ensemble Models (Day 21)\n",
    "LightGBM and XGBoost natively handle large datasets efficiently. We train them on the full dataset with `scale_pos_weight` applied."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if df_raw is not None:\n",
    "    adv_results, adv_models = train_advanced_models(X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val)\n",
    "    display(adv_results)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Final Model Comparison"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if df_raw is not None:\n",
    "    final_comparison = pd.concat([baseline_results, adv_results], ignore_index=True)\n",
    "    final_comparison = final_comparison.sort_values(by='PR-AUC', ascending=False)\n",
    "    display(final_comparison)"
   ]
  }
 ],
